Aurora is a custom-designed relational database engine that forms part of RDS. 
    Rather than an evolution, Aurora significantly replaces much of the traditional MySQL and PostgreSQL architecture in favor of cluster and shared storage architecture
    which is more scalable and resilient with much higher performance

Cluster volume: Max 64 TB, 6 replica, 3 AZs

use base configuration of Cluster
share storage
storage replicte 3 or more AZs
can tolerate 2 failure without write being impacted
3 failures without impact read
auto healing

backtrack can roll back up to 72 hours
    will get an outage but keep all the configuration

parallel queries


aurora global
